To install neovim in Ubuntu:
  run: chmod +x neovim.sh
  then, run: ./neovim.sh

After installed and copied config folder to correct location:
 1. Run nvim and inside nvim run ":PlugInstall" and wait to install plugins
 2. Exit neovim (:q) and run: nvim ~/.config/nvim/init.vim
 3. Delete all quotation mark (") in this file, save file and exit (:wq)
 4. Open nvim again (you will see the installation of CoC) and run ":VimspectorInstal vscode-cpptools" or any adapter you need
 5. Customize your Startify bookmarks in ~/.config/nvim/Plugins-Config/Other.vim 
 6. Done.

 Manual install:
   * install 'neovim'
   * install 'vim-plug' see https://github.com/junegunn/vim-plug

   * install 'nodejs' lastest version + 'npm'
       only Ubuntu:
               curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_current.x | sudo -E bash -
               sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
     install nodejs provider:
        sudo npm install -g neovim

   * install 'python' , 'python-pip' , 'python2' , 'python2-pip'
       only Ubuntu:
               install 'python', 'python-pip' package (python2 + python3 + python3-pip)
               to install python2-pip:
                    wget https://bootstrap.pypa.io/pip/2.7/get-pip.py && sudo python2 get-pip.py
   * install pynvim:
        python2 -m pip install --user --upgrade pynvim 
        python3 -m pip install --user --upgrade pynvim
   * install 'ccls'

 Copy config:
      copy "nvim" folder to /home/nltt/.config/
      Or if you download all Setup:
      cp -r ~/Downloads/Setup_Ubuntu_Full/Setup/app-ubuntu/neovim/nvim ~/.config/

Then see "After install..." above

